postcontent:
* Price Drop *  Up for sale is a rather unique firearm. It is a PSL. (Romak III) that has been reworked into a 16 inch barreled carbine. It was manufactured by waffen works out of TN. Below is a description of the rifle when it was available on atlantic firearms.

" The AK-54Rrifles are built upon category 1 Romanian PSL parts kits, using a special reciever that allows for the use of regular AKM type buttstocks and pistol grips. They also feature a correct, and fully functional scope mount installed on the left side of the reciever. The barrel is shortened to 16.5 inches and is re-profiled, allowing the gas block and handgaurd retainer to be moved rearward, so that standard AKM gas pistons and handgaurds can be used."

Basically they built an AKM in 7.62x54R. This rifle is no longer produced as it seems the import of the parts kits has slowed. I have seen these rifles sell for 1500+, with only one mag and no bayonett. I am offering mine up for 1200 with 6 mags, and a romanian bayonett to go with it, for more close encounters! It's a Rock River Arms LAR-8 (.308), in Mid-length (16") barrel A4 configuration which has a flat top, fwd site base gas block with sling attachment, Hogue grip, 6 position stock. Comes with 3-20round mags and uses the FAL surplus mags which are inexpensive online and at gun shows. The 308 gives you the power and size to hunt large game and gives you a lot more range due to the projectile mass as compared to .223 while also having the ability to be a close combat semi-auto weapon. Also gives you way more muzzle velocity and several feet less bullet drop than the 7.62x39 past 250 yards.

The scope is a Leapers 1x4 combat scope with illuminated red/green reticle on a low profile base which has long eye relief. With a 1x4 you can crank it down and use it like a close combat red dot or bump it up to 4x to take 300 yard shots. The mounts are weaver quick release. The sling is a heavy padded combat sling that adjusts and has neoprene sleeves on the steel buckles so it doesnt make noise or scratch the finish. 200 rounds of federal, 40 rounds of winchester core lock. The nylon bag is padded with a sling to carry on your back with mag pouches in the front. 

I'd like to get $1100 for the rifle and 3 mags.
